usda to conduct survey for avian influenza u.s. agricultur depart anim health offici are conduct a nation survey of live-bird market and auction to check for sign of avian influenza , an infecti viral diseas of poultri , the depart said . the survey will locat poultri dealer and live-bird market that sell live bird directli to the consum and onc the dealer and market are identifi , there will be test to determin ani past or present exposur to avian influenza virus , it said . in 1983-84 , an outbreak of avian influenza in pennsylvania , maryland , virginia and new jersey cost taxpay 65 mln dlr to control and requir the destruct of more than 17 mln bird , it said . the survey is expect to be complet by april 15 .